# Database conventions (SAP-style)

- snake_case; singular table names
- Every table: `<table>_uuid` UUID PK (gen_random_uuid()), `mandt`,
  `created_by`, `created_at`, `changed_by`, `changed_at`
- Tenant tables include `org_uuid` and get an RLS policy in the SAME
  migration that creates the table
- Migrations: forward-only SQL in supabase/migrations/,
  YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql. Never edit an applied migration.
- Business logic in application code, not triggers
